Question: How can I make a button that when clicked, it will open a new activity?
Please using this api: Intent.
Answer:<<<api>>>: Intent
<<<code>>>: Button button = findViewById(R.id.button);
button.setOnClickListener(new View.OnClickListener() {
    @Override
    public void onClick(View v) {
        Intent intent = new Intent(MainActivity.this, SecondActivity.class);
        startActivity(intent);
    }
});
<<<explanation>>>: The Intent class represents an intent to start an Activity.
Question: How can I make a button that when clicked, it will open a new activity and pass data to it?
Please using this api: Intent.
Answer:<<<api>>>: Intent
<<<code>>>: Button button = findViewById(R.id.button);
button.setOnClickListener(new View.OnClickListener() {
    @Override
    public void onClick(View v) {
        Intent intent = new Intent(MainActivity.this, SecondActivity.class);
        intent.putExtra("data", "Hello from MainActivity");
        startActivity(intent);
    }
});
<<<explanation>>>: The putExtra() method of the Intent class adds an extra to the intent.
Question: How can I make a button that when clicked, it will open a new activity and pass data to it and get data from it?
Please using this api: Intent.
Answer:<<<api>>>: Intent
<<<code>>>: Button button = findViewById(R.id.button);
button.setOnClickListener(new View.OnClickListener() {
    @Override
    public void onClick(View v) {
        Intent intent = new Intent(MainActivity.this, SecondActivity.class);
        intent.putExtra("data", "Hello from MainActivity");
        startActivityForResult(intent, 1);
    }
});
<<<explanation>>>: The startActivityForResult() method of the Activity class starts an activity for a result.
